# Developer Documentation
The Dining API is an endpoint that allows you to get information about a given
eatery on Carnegie Mellon's campus.  In particular, we offer time information,
keywords, and a short description you can use in your CMU Dining related
applications.

While more detailed documentation follows, go ahead and try it out by going to
`apis.scottylabs.org/dining/v1/locations` in your favourite browser.

## Version 1
In version 1, there is only one endpoint, at `/locations`.

### GET `/locations`
Request:
```
GET apis.scottylabs.org/api/dining/v1/locations
```

Response format:
```
{
"locations":
    [
        {
            "name": string,
            "description": string,
            "keywords": [string],
            "location": string,
            "times": {
                "monday":
                    [
                        {
                            "start": { "hour": number, "min": number }
                            "end": { "hour": number, "min": number }
                        },
                        ...
                    ],
                "tuesday":
